Check barcode raw count distribution for Ameliaâ€™s data

barcode = read.delim("../data/Barcodes_capitalized.txt", header = FALSE, sep = "\t",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
colnames(barcode) = c("seq", "rs","unknown")
index4 = read.delim("../data/Index4_V2.txt", header = FALSE, sep = "\t", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
index7 = read.delim("../data/Index7_V2.txt", header = FALSE, sep = "\t", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
colnames(index4) = c("seq", "count")
colnames(index7) = c("seq","count")
hist(log(index4$count))

hist(log(index7$count))

sum(index4$count)
## [1] 64483658
sum(index7$count)
## [1] 73533008

suppose remove reads greater than exp(6) for both dataset with documented barcodes

index4.1 = index4[index4$count < exp(6) & is.element(index4$seq, barcode[,1]),]
index7.1 = index7[index7$count < exp(6) & is.element(index7$seq, barcode[,1]),]
index4.1 = data.frame(index4.1, nor_count = index4.1$count/sum(index4.1$count)*1000000)
index7.1 = data.frame(index7.1, nor_count = index7.1$count/sum(index7.1$count)*1000000)

# Figure 1.1

plot(density(index4.1$nor_count),xlim=c(0,20))

# Figure 1.2

plot(density(index7.1$nor_count),xlim=c(0,20))

index4_with_barcode = index4[is.element(index4$seq, barcode$seq),]
index7_with_barcode = index7[is.element(index7$seq, barcode$seq),]
sum(index4_with_barcode$count)
## [1] 42023669
sum(index7_with_barcode$count)
## [1] 48177385
index4_with_barcode = data.frame(index4_with_barcode, standardized_count = index4_with_barcode$count/sum(index4_with_barcode$count)*1000000)
index7_with_barcode = data.frame(index7_with_barcode, standardized_count = index7_with_barcode$count/sum(index7_with_barcode$count)*1000000)

plot(density(index4_with_barcode$count))

plot(density(index7_with_barcode$count))

plot(density(index4_with_barcode$standardized_count))

plot(density(index7_with_barcode$standardized_count))

index4_7_with_barcode = merge(index4_with_barcode, index7_with_barcode, by.x = "seq", by.y = "seq")
plot(log(index4_7_with_barcode$count.x,2), log(index4_7_with_barcode$count.y,2))

plot(log(index4_7_with_barcode$standardized_count.x,2), log(index4_7_with_barcode$standardized_count.y,2))
abline(0,1)

index4_7_with_barcode = data.frame(index4_7_with_barcode,activiy = index4_7_with_barcode$standardized_count.y/index4_7_with_barcode$standardized_count.x)
index4_7_with_barcode = index4_7_with_barcode[order(index4_7_with_barcode$activiy, decreasing = FALSE),]
plot(seq(1,nrow(index4_7_with_barcode)), log(index4_7_with_barcode$activiy,2))
